video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: So I wrote a prescription for antibiotics for Aiden.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Okay.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Um, I did wanna talk to you though. I'm a little bit concerned looking through his chart of how many ear infections he's had recently. And I-I noticed that you had checked the box that someone's smoking in the home. So I was wondering if you can tell me a little more about that.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Well, um, It's just me and him and I do smoke. Um, I try really hard not to smoke around him, but I-I've been smoking for 10 years except when I was pregnant with him. But it-- everything is so stressful being a single mom and-and my having a full-time job. And so it's just-- that's why I started smoking again.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: You have a lot of things going on and smoking's kind of a way to relax and destress.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Yeah. Some people have a glass of wine. I have a cigarette.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Sure. And it sounds like you're trying not to smoke around him. Why did you make that decision?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: I know it's not good for him. I mean, I've read those things about ear infections and asthma and stuff and-and, uh, but other kids have ear infections and their parents don't smoke.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: So on the one hand, you're worried about how your smoking might be affecting him and on the other hand, you're not so sure if it's really the smoking that's causing these problems?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Right. Yeah. I mean, he doesn't have asthma. Yeah. He-- I don't-- he hasn't had a lot of other problems that his other friends have, so. And I've thought about quitting before in the past, but I just don't- I just don't see how it's possible right now.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: What made you decide to quit smoking when you were pregnant?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Well, he was inside me and we were sharing everything and I knew that he would get some of that. And I didn't-- I just didn't-didn't think I could live with myself if something happened to him.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Right now, though, it feels almost too difficult to even manage or even to try?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Yeah, exactly.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: How were you successful when you quit before?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: I don't know. I-I think about it now, I don't even know how I did it. I just- I just did it. You know, I just- I just couldn't imagine like him not being born or going into labor early-

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Mm-hmm.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: -and-and him having problems and stuff like that, all the stuff that they talk about with women who smoke. So I-- that was just enough to-to say, "Okay, you know what, I'm-I'm not going to risk that." so.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Mm-hmm. The risks were so scary then that you were able to stop?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Yeah.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: But they don't feel as scary to you now?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: No, I mean, we're two separate people. And like I said, I don't, I try really hard not to smoke around him. I'm pretty good about that. I-I don't let other people smoke around him. Um, so I, you know.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: You're doing the best you can do.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Yes.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Okay. But it sounds to me too like part of you really does want to quit?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Yeah. I-I know that I need to, and I, you know, keep every new year I say, "Okay, this year I'm gonna quit smoking" but then something happens and it-it just doesn't. And quitting doesn't happen.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: It's on your to-do list. It's just not making it to the top?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Yeah.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: If you did decide to quit on a scale of 1 to 10, where 1 is not at all confident, and you don't think you could do it and 10 is you feel pretty certain that you could, where do you think you fall right now?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Probably like a 5 . Kind of in the unsure area. Like I know I've done it before, so I know I can do it, but at the same time, it just seems really hard. And it's not the same situation.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Well, what made you say five rather than two or three?

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: I know- I know all the ways it's bad for me. And I don't want him to grow up thinking that it's okay to smoke. Um, so I know I need to, especially before he gets old enough to understand what mommy's doing, but I just don't know if I can do it.

video_title: The Effective Physician: Motivational Interviewing Demonstration
utterance_text: Okay. So it sounds like you have a lot of reasons why you'd like to quit. You have been successful quitting in the past, and right now you're just feeling a little bit hesitant about your ability to do it?
